name: Hernan Romero
bio:
Romero's 'Un Segundo Una Vida' brought his flamenco and Latin-based jazz to new realms with the addition of more complex orchestration and additional instrumentation.

 

Including the melodic strings of a chamber orchestra, and a wide array of penetrating vocals. Romero's CD, 'Duende', hit number 6 on the Billboard charts (World Music).

 

Romero continues to captivate audiences around the world.  Hernan was born into an Argentinian family as both his parents were musicians. He was influenced by his mother, a latin Grammy and Lifetime Achievement winner and his father, a producer.

 

At age 9, he learned to play the guitar with his natural talent. He then gained a formal education at Manhattan School of Music and pursued music as a career. He continued make a name for himself and was a Grammy winner in 2001 for his album 'Un Segundo Una Vida'.
exp:
Hernan's career consists of playing with top artists from Stevie Nicks until he took the path of more instrumental style music where he went on to play with some of the world's best guitarists like John McLaughlin and Al Di Meola.

 

He has pushed the limits of genre as his music consists of elements of : Latin, Mediterranean, Middle Eastern, Flamenco mixed with jazz, fusion and classical

name: Leify Green
bio:
This album is a unique listening experience from start to finish. Lyrically, it is an exploration of pain, darkness, and hope. It was recorded in various studios all over the United States, and it cuts across multiple musical styles and genres. "Set Sail" is a record unlike any I have ever heard. It breaks the conventional rules of album production, and I am proud of that. It was recorded over a span of several years, in various studios with different musicians and different mixing engineers.

 

In some places it is thoroughly edited, fine-tuned, and dressed up, while in others it is completely naked. It is a story of pain and loneliness, but it is also a story of unremitting hope. It is an intimate, authentic piece of myself.

 

Much like my live performances, I am simultaneously excited and terrified to share it with you.

 

Set sail on a musical odyssey with Leify Green And The Various Vikings! Nestled in a unique vessel of original songs, improvised jams, and reimagined smash hits, singer-songwriter Leify Green and his versatile crew will lead you on an unforgettable voyage across the vast open seas between genres as diverse as Folk, Pop, Rock, Reggae, Blues, R&B, Jazz, Swing, Country, Hip-hop, Appalachian, Celtic, Latin, and beyond.
exp:
Leify Green And The Various Vikings are available in solo, duo, trio, four-piece, and five-piece band formats.

Catch Leify Green single-handed and he will entertain you and your party with tales from beyond the horizon in between soulful songs, creative covers, and even a few fiddle tunes. Be prepared for dancing, laughter, and tears, sometimes all at the same time.

bio:

exp:
Gen “Genzo” Rubin is a producer, songwriter, artist, engineer, animator, photographer & videographer who can jump from genre to genre with equal ability, as seen in his diverse body of work. However, he is not merely versatile. He commands respect with each of his forays into different musical genres, be it Pop, R&B, Latin, Rock, Gospel, Dance, or Soundtrack work. 

He has directed music videos that were in heavy rotation on MTV, and has shot single artwork for artists on major labels. His accomplishments include the Grammy-nominated R&B song, "Don't Waste Your Time," by Mary J. Blige and Aretha Franklin, his work on contemporary gospel artist Phase II (also Grammy-nominated), the worldwide hit, "Aqui Estoy Yo," by Luis Fonsi, which won Genzo a Latin Grammy for Song of the Year, the #1 pop hit, "Don't Say Goodbye," by Paulina Rubio, rap song, "Yummy," by Chelo featuring the legendary Too $hort, and the dance chart topper “Until We Meet Again,” with Diana Ross. His first foray into the Latin market with EMI Latin's DJ Kane garnered him a Latin Grammy nomination for Producer of the Year.

After splitting his career between Los Angeles and New York, he is back in his hometown, Seattle, composing new works, developing artists and shooting and editing videos from his new studio. He is now taking the leap into the metaverse, creating NFT’s of new works blending all his skills.

name: Jeff Korb
bio:
Florida guitarist/songwriter, Jeff Korb, laments he learned to play guitar in the mid/late 80s whenit was more of a full-contact sport and art form of the time.

He jokingly reflects, that his favoritesongs were ranked by which ones had the coolest solos.

A detour from music into a banking career (life happens) brought Korb a new outlook.

Stepping back from seriously playing music for so long and just listening and enjoying, created anenvironment where I was hearing songs with a completely different ear.

It took me back toplaying guitar to then writing songs and finally pushing forth with a new band."
exp:
I found myself listening to songs and wondering how to put myself in the mindset of thesongwriter," he says. "I wanted to think the way they were thinking and understand theircreative process.

I wanted to take that knowledge and apply it to the ideas I had. It made mesuch a better musician.

I stopped being concerned as a guitar player about how fast I could playa few licks in a guitar solo and focused on creating music and songs people wanted to hear.

That was when I stopped being a guy that could play guitar and became a musician that plays guitar."

From Motown to Bebop, to Broadway andMetal along with everything in-between, music was always around. His musicalinspirations are vast but some of his favorite bass players are Paul McCartney, John P.Jones, James Jamerson, John Decon, Robert De Leo and Steve Harris, along with so manyother amazing talented low enders.
exp:
Before joining the band Three Shot Limit, Ross Kevles was mostly known for his widevariety of cover band experience. Most notably the cover band Whiskey Straight, whowas sponsored by Fireball, which gained popularity in Virginia Beach circa 2011-2015playing hundreds of performances at every local venue that supported live music.

Rossshows no fear when it comes to assisting in back-up vocals, bringing in his contagiousenergy, and always seems to get the crowd jumping along with him while he's on stage. While serving in the US Navy, for over 20 years, Ross played all over the world bringinghis style and creative process everywhere he played which ranged from dive bars andfestivals to every size concert hall, he has played to every type of crowd .

This name, bestowed upon Rahimah in a traditional ceremony, symbolizes a deep connection to her calling. The duo brings renewed energy and purpose to their musical journey, embracing inspiration and curiosity in their lifelong union.

Rahimah and Abel’s romance has modern fairytale vibes. Rahimah and Abel's love story started in the late 1980s, and after years of crossing paths, they officially began dating in high school.

Their shared passion for music led to a lifelong collaboration, with Abel becoming a songwriter and studio engineer, while Rahimah focused on poetry and singing.

name: Road Waves
bio:
Road Waves' distinctive sound and exuberance have not gone unnoticed, with accolades such as 'Best New Group' and 'Best Jazz Group' at the 2016 Niagara Music Awards, culminating in a coveted Diamond award in the 2020 Niagara Falls Readers Choice Awards.

Their single ‘Frog Rock’ has earned a coveted spot on Spotify’s ‘Modern Jam Band’ editorial playlist, affirming their resonance within the contemporary music landscape.

Road Waves has been a revelation, entrancing audiences across North America with their unbeatable spirit and musical flair for a decade. They invite you on an intimate and thrilling journey with every song, leaving an indelible impression on all who partake.


Conceived a decade ago by visionary front man Ji Sharp, the band has swiftly ascended as a tour de force in the realm of live performances. This fiery unit has a deep bond with their audience, with each performance delivering an energetic and emotional experience that captivates and energizes listeners. Their live shows skillfully mix precision and spontaneity, creating a memorable experience that lingers long after the music ends.
exp:
Experience the sonic adventure that is Road Waves; a dynamic ensemble seamlessly melding the raw energy of rock, the groove of funk, and the sophistication of jazz into an electrifying genre-defying fusion.

Their discography is marked by ingenuity and a relentless pursuit of musical excellence, with two critically acclaimed independent albums: 'The Lighthouse' (2015) and 'Red Sun Rising' (2018).

Their artistic prowess shines through in popular singles 'Hometown' (2022), 'Small World' (2022), and the most recent 'Frog Rock' (2023), each track underscoring their diverse capabilities and steadfast dedication.

name: Michael ‚ÄúMP‚Äù Paul
bio:
Raised in the heart of St. Petersburg, Florida’s south side, MP’s journey was fraught with challenges. Growing up with his father behind bars, he found role models among local drug dealers.

MP’s mother worked at local concert venues, introducing him to a wide array of live music genres, aiming to provide a positive outlet and steer him clear of the streets. Music soon evolved into an obsession, a refuge from the surrounding crime and addiction.
exp:
A captivating wordsmith, MP delivers smooth, buttery vocals, encapsulating equal parts pain and inspiration. MP’s discography will take you through life’s highs and lows.

He’s an urban poet with a niche for resilience. Each track breathes authenticity and is a reminder to all that anyone can prevail in the face of adversity. 

After serving nearly a decade in federal prison for conspiracy drug charges, MP was determined to deliver a dream deferred. He learned to transform his hustle and avoid the pitfalls of the streets.

In 2020, he launched Live Struggle Legacy - a tribute to Timothy “Big Baby” Lewis who lost his life behind bars, as a result of a negligent prison healthcare system. Live Struggle Legacy is a platform for artists with the mission of shedding light on injustice while inspiring positive change.
works: MP creates movement driven music with the mind-set of unity and collaboration.

name: Kirk DeSoto
bio:
Kirk DeSoto is a singer/songwriter who quit music for about a decade but was brought back to music via the Web3 music space. 

He began singing in choirs when he was very young and performed in the Opera Carmen around the age of 10. He played piano as a child as well but eventually shifted to the guitar, taking inspiration from a childhood friend and starting a band with him in high school.

Kirk garnered a lot of inspiration for his early music from growing up near Seattle during the height of the grudge era. He interned at Sony Music Studios in New York City in 2000 for an audio engineering program and subsequently recorded 2 independently produced albums there.

After much touring in New York City during the early 2000’s he eventually got disaffected with the New York City independent music scene and the industry as a whole, much of which was a pay to play system. He left New York in 2012 and slowly became less and less active doing anything musically until eventually he stopped playing guitar and barely sang anymore.
exp:
As far as Kirk was concerned half a decade later, music was forever behind him and he had no plans of being musical again. He discovered Bitcoin in 2011 but never got into the space or invested in it at the time, but eventually started his deep dive into cryptocurrency in 2016.

He started getting into NFT’s in 2021 and was subsequently introduced to the idea of adding music to an image and releasing it on a blockchain. Around April of 2022 he discovered a group of singer/songwriters, beginning with Violetta Zironi, selling their music for Ethereum and combining the idea of gamified collectorship with art and music using blockchain as the medium.

He started to become an avid collector of many musicians in the Web3 space, and the inspiration garnered by spending a lot of time engaged in the Web3 music space, inspired him to start getting back into music. By October of 2022 Kirk not only launched his first music NFT collection but also played live the following month for the first time in almost 11 years in London, UK at an event hosted by musician Josh Savage.

Through this time he really got involved in the gamification, tokenomics and drop strategy mechanisms of music NFT’s, leaning on the many prior years he spent delving deep into the tokenomics of cryptocurrencies, beginning in 2016. Kirk began advising many creators and artists in the Web3 space starting in 2022 about collection gamification and drop mechanics.

In 2023 TokenTraxx brought Kirk on as an advisor. Web3 has truly changed Kirk’s life and he loves helping and educating people about blockchain and the Web3 space in general.

His goal is to help build a new music paradigm, combining the concept of artists owning their own creations via staying independent and utilizing the tools that blockchain technology has to offer to help foster the principles of decentralization and self-ownership.

Goldilocks, aka yesiamgoldilocks, is a Reggaeton and Hip-Hop artist from NYC, by way of Asturias, Spain. Her hit record 'Saab Story' debuted on Spotify's 'New Music Friday Latin' Playlist and her first fully Spanish record, 'La Que No,' was featured on NPR’s 'Alt.Latino' Playlist.

She was invited to do one-liners for iHeart Radio, telling her "coming out" story for 'National Coming Out Day 2020,' had the honor to perform in the Amazon Music 'Together At Home’ Concert series to premiere her single 'Bañador,' and has been featured in media outlets such as CNN's “Zona Pop,” Univision / Uforia Austin, Dash Radio, and many others.

Goldilocks is a multi-instrumentalist producer that uses her life-long background in music to write and compose fun, sexy, fully bilingual music that makes people feel confident and understood, drawing inspiration from her own experiences, as well as from artists she admires like J Balvin, Kanye West, Pharrell and Bad Bunny, to name a few.

Her debut album ‘Future Famous,’ which was recorded in the midst of the pandemic, features lyrics in English as well as Spanish and is available for streaming and purchase now. Her freshman album boasts 12 self-produced songs, along with one track produced by L O U I S M E.

exp:
ANGL is a genre-bending electronic artist and immersive performer redefining what a live set can be. Known for fusing hypnotic beats with custom-built, audio-reactive visuals, ANGL creates multi-sensory journeys that blur the line between sound and sight — turning every performance into a living piece of digital art.

Drawing inspiration from cyberpunk aesthetics, glitch art, and underground rave culture, ANGL doesn’t just play music — they build atmospheres. Their sets pulse with energy, emotion, and intentional design, making each show feel like a step into another dimension. Whether commanding the stage at house parties, outdoor music festivals or digital metaverse events, ANGL leaves audiences spellbound and craving more.

Rooted in innovation and driven by a love for sonic experimentation, ANGL is on a mission to make live music feel like the future — immersive, unforgettable, and deeply connected.

name: AttaBotty
bio: As a web3 enthusiast, AttaBotty co-founded the ZAO, a decentralized, community-driven hub that empowers independent creators with tools and support to reclaim control over their work, data, and fan connections. Additionally, he contributes as a member of the Temple artist collective as a performing artist. His commitment to building community in web3 also shines through his active participation in various artist communities, such as @nftrecordshop and @onchainrecords, where he shares his original music, animations, and professional insights. Together with his wife, @Da__Nici, he co-founded AttaBotty Productions, a studio specializing in custom animations and music. Their studio collaborates with a diverse range of creatives, including musicians, visual artists, animators, and game developers.
exp: AttaBotty is a composer, multi-instrumentalist, and audiovisual storyteller whose name(a phonetic play on "out of body") reflects his commitment to creating immersive artistic experiences. THrough theatrical visuals, sonic effects, and captivating music, he guides his audience to the core of his art's message.  His ability to animate and play instruments like the flute, piano, guitar and purcussion has been essential in shaping his diverse repertiore, fusin 2D/3D animations with live instrumental elements, EDM, Lo-Fi, and cinematic ochestra. While much of his work is serious, not all compositions are somber, reflecting AttaBotty's vivacious outlook on life.
works: Since joining Web3 in May 2022, AttaBotty has sold over 10,000 NFT's, collaborated with more than 10 web3 artists, earned a place on the Base Pnchain Registry, and had his animation selected for he NFT.NYC 2024 animation category.
hobbies: Artistic Message: As an artist, AttaBotty is driven by a mission to showcase the married dualistic nature of existence. This theme is prominently featured in his art. His affinity for this subject ultimately stemmed from his battles with physical ailments. Living with systemic illnesses, including SLE (Lupus), Sjogren's, and Fibromyalgia, AttaBotty has discovered the importance of peace and self-acceptance to maintain his functionality. While his health challenges initially shaped his perspective, it was the out-of-body experiences during his toughest moments that led him to these invaluable lessons. Through his audiovisual art, he aspires to share these insights with receptive individuals, aiming to contribute to a more conscious, responsible, and compassionate world.

exp:
"Rhyme. Grind. Dataway."

Redefining Hip-Hop with Heart, Data, and Destiny.

Mozay Calloway is a New York-bred rapper, visionary, and solo father redefining hip-hop through resilience and innovation.

From the streets of New York to the global stage, Mozay’s journey—fueled by the loss of his late wife to breast cancer—transforms grief into powerful music. Blending Hip-Hop, Rap, and Jazz Rap influences, his storytelling shines in tracks like 'The Big Payoff', 'Say What Now', 'Seat at the Table', and the upcoming 'Dear Vikki' album.

As CEO of We The CEO and a Web3 pioneer, Mozay crafts real-world anthems with blockchain utility, empowering communities through Bitcoin HipHop and BNice Projects. His initiatives, including the Intergalactic Academy of Arts and Sciences and the IZAYDA shoe line, showcase an evolving empire built on creativity, empowerment, and ownership.

With the Freedom Festival Tour hitting 16 cities in 2025 and strategic partnerships across Web3 and traditional music, Mozay’s 'Rhyme, Grind, and Dataway' ethos is ushering hip-hop into a bold new future.

Join the movement.
